column1: #Weekly Topic# Recommend Your Favorite App! Win Honor Earphone!
column2: 2Here are my Favourite Apps!Image Editing :Snapseed : Provides professional photo editing options in a very simple and neat way. ( No Ads )PicsArt Photo Studio : Another Amazing App! Used it before using Snapseed. Editing options are good but it's not easy to save in gallery directly.Browser :When it comes to Browser, my favourite one is firefox.I use only Firefox and Firefox Focus, which is light weight and never stores anything.No privacy, when using other browsers.Weather :I used to ask Google Assistant for weather most of the times. For deatiled data, I check AccuWeather.Heath/ Fitness :For this, Huawei health follows me in default. It counts my steps approx without band and I never tried any other app in this category.Using Insight Timer app for meditations.Eagerly waiting to see what others are using.Discussions and replies are welcomeSame here. I'm using Snapseed as well.It's really powerful and has a lot of features. Amazing !!It's an great app :DThanks! Did you shared yours ?No not yet. But by today evening I'll post

column1: We Are Recruiting Honor Geek Team Members. If you are a tech geek, Apply Here!
column2: 2Hi I am Deepak, I am a tech enthusiastic and a btech student who is also a free lance front-end web developer. I always think about technology and new software update and everything about tech.Mobile's that I am using?Honor 7x,Honor 9 lite, Smartron srt phone.Which topic I am interested?EMUI update features,E-Commerce,Android Platform,Honor intelligent Products,Smartphones, Drones,Geek events.Why I am eligible?Ans:-I think I am eligible for this because I always read tech news rather than any other newsIf you see my phone I have all the tech news providing apps like beebom,Android Authority,Android central, freely,make use of etc.If you see my google feed 90% of the feed contains news about technology. I always search about technology.I have started a blog with technews but ended up stopping it due to lack of advertising skills.Threads that I have created?Sorry for that I haven't created any threads till now but I think I am a good Tech Geek.     Thank you,Hope you will accept my request.All the best Deepak! Expecting some posts about tech from you in Off-topic section.

column1: We Are Recruiting Honor Geek Team Members. If you are a tech geek, Apply Here!
column2: 3Hi, I am Athivignesha Software Engineer from Chennai, living in Bangalore now.Ever since I saw amobile phone for the first time when I was 12 years old, I knew that mobilephones have always held a special place in my heart.I currently use aHonor 7XAreas I'm interested in:I keep myselfupdated on EMUI features, have explored and researched a ton about them and Ihave created my own themes for personal use by scavenging bits and pieces fromseveral themes. I also read extensively about all the latest and greatestthings happening in the smartphone market.I believe I ameligible for this post, because I understand that, I have a very stronginfluence on the smartphone purchases of most of my friends, and even theirfriends and families, because of the my personalized suggestions for every userbased on their needs and usage patterns. Also, it is almost every time me whoinforms my friends in chat groups about the latest interesting news in techworld.I have explored theEMUI features extensively and have a very good knowledge on Honor phones.I am sorry that Ihave not posted any threads so far since I am new to Honor/EMUI, but I intendto change that, since I am mighty impressed by the EMUI.

column2: 7About Me :-I am a tech enthusiastic person from the very beginning. I always take my eyes on the latest tech trends, updates, news gadgets etc.Why To Choose Me :-Well I am Tech YouTuber from India and I run a channel named "IndiCoder" which has currently over 38.8k subscribers at th time of posting this. I make videos on Tips And Tricks, Apps, Smartphones and Gadget reviews. I review in Hindi and all of my videos have over 90% Likes ratio. I have previosuly made Honor 6x review which got really nice response. Also all of my videos are shot on Honor 6x because I know how good the camera is.What To Expect :-One Thing To Swear :-Since I shoot videos proffesionally so I won't be able to post about the Software updates in the community here. But I am a very active member on the Facebook Honor Groups and also there will be no delay from my side in terms of VIDEOS.

column1: AI-Powered Phone, Why you should buy it?
column2: 3One thing I want to add is that if you are changing over from an amoled/super amoled display mobile then you will feel the difference. You will miss the amoled experience. And super amoled is good for battery saving too.To be frank I miss a super amoled display on my view 10, but as you told the view 10 display is not that bad. I am getting adjusted.One more thing is the brightness management in view 10 is a failure. When using indoor you have to keep the brightness level around 35-50% which is not acceptable. This drains battery too fast.I have used other mobiles where in the same room brightness of the screen is set to below 30%.If you reduce brightness and use, then the view 10 experience won't amaze you.Agree. Bro.

column1: [The fist batch list is annouced now] We are looking for Honor Community Moderators, Apply Here!
column2: 4Hello Captain Zoro and Team! Thank You for this wonderful opportunity..  For a Tech Enthusiast a mainstream desire always stays in the heart to be a part of an initiative like this and what's better than getting such opportunity from his/her favourite brand.  Who am I? I am a student, a freelance photographer and a tech reviewer/enthusiast who is always after to try out new devices and recommend to people around.Categories I am fit for: Photography, Off-Topic, Honor 9 Lite.  Why Photography? I have been practicing photography since 16 months and I have fairly enough experience to SHOW, ENHANCE, SHARE, the artwork and knowledge to make others capable of doing wonderful things from their Honor Cameras.  Why Off-Topic? I have handled Off Topic technical threads and facebook groups with audience up to 100 thousand people. pretty experienced dealing with the acceptable and non acceptable level of things in the community.Why Honor 9 Lite? As I have won a Honor 9 Lite in the recent contest organised by Honor Team, I am *** sure that my fascination would make myself dig deeper in the device, observe it, understand it completely and since I am good at clearing doubts and queries of people regarding tech, I feel like I can be the one to keep people satisfied by letting none of their queries unsolved.Bonus Benefits: 1.) Really good at promoting and recommending devices as my audience listens to me. 2.) Always keep the spammers out of the community and would delete those stupid posts ASAP to keep the community clean. 3.) Experienced with managing a private tech forum and a website for almost 7-8 months.4.) Got a lot of time to stay active.5.) Determined to make a recognition for myself and my institution.  PicWiz is always here to make himself useful!All the best Dude!Thanks pal!Good luck. Thanks a lot Christine :)I would definitely vote for him if i can, the man who won last year's photography contest by max vote and got Honor 6X for himself. Really have skills in photography and a large audience which listens to him. Best of luck Mate

column1: We are looking for Honor Product Team Members, Apply Here!
column2: 3Hi @ZoroI am Aravind M Nair, from Kerala - The land of Hills and Spices , a proud member of the Honor family since 2014, and currently working as a Mobile App Developer. I have been there with the honor from the very begining when the Huawei sub-brand launched in India, and at that time i was a grad. student. I was attracted by the looks,specs and unique pricing of the device when it was first launched in Indian Market. My short bio says, "Analog at Birth, Digital by Design", simply because of my endless love towards gadgets and tech which is unending.It all started with a Honor 4x.Yes, At the year of 2014, when i was thinking to switch to a real "Smart Phone", one of my friend named 'Sijo' who is using Honor 6 at that time suggested me about Honor 4x. Considering his suggestion, i researched more about the brand and the device and ended up in my final decision to by the beauty.My Journey with Honor:https://club.hihonor.com/in/offtopic.209/my-journey-with-honor-from-2014-to-2017.8855From there, honor was not just a phone in hand, but more of like a family. i used to be active in Honor groups in facebook, provide support to users in trouble, collected data regarding the bugs and reporting ... and did whatever i can, so that my little help to someone can contribute to the honor community.As time passes, new smartphones emerged in to market, and Currently, i own 3 Honor devices. Honor 4x, Honor 5c, Honor 6x.------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Honor 6x: My Gaming partner-https://club.hihonor.com/in/honor-6x-double-or-nothing--phone.305/my-story-with-honor6x---a-great-allrounder-in-the-midrange.97213------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------I am a part-time or hobbyist blogger and a passioante youtuber, who creates content and shares in the Internet whenever i gets time. I love writing about tech stuff, provide support to users and also an EMUI device expert. (awarded asTECH NINJA by Honor CLub India for my contribution)My blog: http://aravindmnair.blogMy Youtube Channel:https://www.youtube.com/c/TheYoutubeTechMy areas of Interest , if asked for is almost in everything likeHonor Products, Tips and Tricks, Tech Class, Live Q/A, Resources, Themes, EMUI Update, Off-Topic, Photography.I have also won awards earlier for my photography skils and participated in almost every Photography contests conducted by Honor. You can check my Instagram handle, where i have showcase my photography skills, mostly by Honor devices.-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Instagram handle:https://instagram.com/aravi.nairFacebook Group managed by me & Honor friends:https://www.facebook.com/groups/honor5cIndia/------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Some of my Threads in Honor Community:https://club.hihonor.com/in/honor-9-lite.321/honor-9-lite-glacier-gray-coming-soon.85165https://club.hihonor.com/in/honor-7x.315/honor-7x--now-proudly-made-in-india.85159https://club.hihonor.com/in/offtopic.209/morethan-700000-apps-removed-from-google-playstore-in-2017.85155https://club.hihonor.com/in/honor-9-lite.321/honor-9-lite--expectations--the-stylish-built-quad-camera-smartphone.69989 We are the Brave

column1: We are looking for Honor Product Team Members, Apply Here!
column2: 5Hello Captain Zoro and Team! Thank You for this wonderful opportunity..  For a Tech Enthusiast a mainstream desire always stays in the heart to be a part of an initiative like this and what's better than getting such opportunity from his/her favourite brand.Devices I use: HTC ONE M7 DUAL, NUBIA Z9 MINI, HONOR 9 Lite *incoming*  Who am I? I am a student, a freelance photographer and a tech reviewer/enthusiast who is always after to try out new devices and recommend to people around.Categories I am fit for: ALL THE RESPONSILITIES MENTIONED ABOVE TO BE HONESTLY PRECISE.  Why Me? I have been practicing photography since 17 months and I have fairly enough experience toSHOW,ENHANCE,SHARE, the artwork and knowledge to make others capable of doing wonderful things from their Honor Cameras. I have worked as a gadget reviewer for a private website and have plenty of experience. I am very friendly and capable enough to answer queries of everyone. Since I have great ability to satisfy people because of my tech backgroud and experience, I am definitely fit for this opportunity.  I have handled Off Topic technical threads and facebook groups with audience up to 100 thousand people. pretty experienced dealing with the acceptable and non acceptable level of things in the community. As I have won a Honor 9 Lite in the recent contest organised by Honor Team, I am sure that my fascination would make myself dig deeper in the device, observe it, understand it completely and since I am good at clearing doubts and queries of people regarding tech, I feel like I can be the one to keep people satisfied by letting none of their queries unsolved. Bonus Benefits: 1.)Really good at promoting and recommending devices as my audience listens to me. 2.)Always keep the spammers out of the community and would delete those stupid posts ASAP to keep the community clean. 3.)Experienced with managing a private tech forum and a website for almost 7-8 months. 4.)Got a lot of time to stay active. 5.)Determined to make a recognition for myself and my institution.MY RECENT ARTICLE  PicWiz is always here to make himself useful!

column1: [The fist batch list is annouced now] We are looking for Honor Community Moderators, Apply Here!
column2: 4Hello Captain Zoro and Team! Thank You for this wonderful opportunity..  For a Tech Enthusiast a mainstream desire always stays in the heart to be a part of an initiative like this and what's better than getting such opportunity from his/her favourite brand.  Who am I? I am a student, a freelance photographer and a tech reviewer/enthusiast who is always after to try out new devices and recommend to people around.Categories I am fit for: Photography, Off-Topic, Honor 9 Lite.  Why Photography? I have been practicing photography since 16 months and I have fairly enough experience to SHOW, ENHANCE, SHARE, the artwork and knowledge to make others capable of doing wonderful things from their Honor Cameras.  Why Off-Topic? I have handled Off Topic technical threads and facebook groups with audience up to 100 thousand people. pretty experienced dealing with the acceptable and non acceptable level of things in the community.Why Honor 9 Lite? As I have won a Honor 9 Lite in the recent contest organised by Honor Team, I am *** sure that my fascination would make myself dig deeper in the device, observe it, understand it completely and since I am good at clearing doubts and queries of people regarding tech, I feel like I can be the one to keep people satisfied by letting none of their queries unsolved.Bonus Benefits: 1.) Really good at promoting and recommending devices as my audience listens to me. 2.) Always keep the spammers out of the community and would delete those stupid posts ASAP to keep the community clean. 3.) Experienced with managing a private tech forum and a website for almost 7-8 months.4.) Got a lot of time to stay active.5.) Determined to make a recognition for myself and my institution.  PicWiz is always here to make himself useful!All the best Dude!Thanks pal!Good luck. Thanks a lot Christine :)I would definitely vote for him if i can, the man who won last year's photography contest by max vote and got Honor 6X for himself. Really have skills in photography and a large audience which listens to him. Best of luck Mate

column1: We are looking for Honor Product Team Members, Apply Here!
column2: 8About Me :-I am Chandan Saxena. I have a technical background. So I can easily understand technical terms and help user in their way. I am using honor devices when Micromax started a era of custom rom with Yureka phone. At that time flash sale was started and many were buying that phone. I searched on internet about that phone and while seraching honor introduces honor 4x in the market. I felt this phone has better camera and battery backup. My friends suggested me not to take honor phones as this is new company in India but I knew Honor is Sub brand of Huawei and most the telecommunication equipment are used in India of Huawei. So I decided to buy honor 4x. Trust me this is the best device that time. From then I bought honor 5c, honor 6x. Now I am usinhg honor 9 lite.  I participated in honor 4x and honor 5c beta team to make EMUI better and now waiting for honor 9 lite beta recuritment to help honor team to provide bug free update.It'll be a great opportunity for me to help in this huge community because I have good knowledge about honor phones, EMUI and tips and tricks and can solve the user problems.

column1: Are You Good at Photographing? We are Recruiting Photography Team Members!
column2: 6Hello Captain Zoro and Team! Thank You for this wonderful opportunity..  For a Tech Enthusiast a mainstream desire always stays in the heart to be a part of an initiative like this and what's better than getting such opportunity from his/her favourite brand.  Who am I? I am a student, a freelance photographer and a tech reviewer/enthusiast who is always after to try out new devices and recommend to people around. DEVICE I USE: HTC ONE M7 DUAL, ZTE NUBIA Z9 MINI and *HONOR 9 LITE *awaiting to recieve, won in Contest Change for Better, it will be replaced with Htc one m7 dual.  Why applying for Photography? I have been practicing photography since 17 months and I have fairly enough experience toSHOW,ENHANCE,SHARE, the artwork and knowledge to make others capable of doing wonderful things from their Honor Cameras. I have a team of freelancers and we do professional shooting as our passion. Since I am a traveller I can write travel stories with some great images. My artwork has been a part of Exhibitions and most importantly I have won titles too! I have many featuring of my smartphone photography as well as conceptual photography. I do have professional photography capabilities as I arrange photography workshops for beginners so yes! I can share few of my untold secrets.. :)Some Achievements:Featured in Various Smartphone photography instagram pages.Winner at Honor 6X Photographhy Contest.2 Inspirational Bagde and 2 awards achiever at YouPic Community.Winner at Delhi Garden Tourism Festival Photography Contest.Won few online photography contests.Featured in PAU Art Gallery Exhibition.Runner up at one LYPG Photo Contest (Facebook). Here are my Few Photography Threads.THREAD 1THREAD 2THREAD 3I call myself PHOTO WIZARD<- CLICK TO KNOW MOREHave a look at My recent article in community as I have enough experience as a content creator as well! PicWiz is always here to make himself useful!Although I have applied too but I'll vote for him if I canThanks brother! I vote for you too! I really want to work with you in team :D

column1: [The fist batch list is annouced now] We are looking for Honor Community Moderators, Apply Here!
column2: 8Hi @ZoroI'm Adi(Member since 2k16)Thank you for this opportunity.As a tech geek I'm always happy to help & support this communityI'm an honor User & a Great Fan of this amazing brand since 2k13.My first device was Honor Bee, thn Honor 4x, Honor 5x, Honor 8., CURRENTLY using honor 9lite.From honor 4x I'm handling many groups Related with Honor devices & Tech.I was Working for Honor team under @Sameer_Paul sir(He supported me a lot)I think I'm good at helping everyone, as a Student I will Try my best To Grow This Community to Its BestI would likeModerate These SectionsEMUI Beta:-Beta(tester) , this word belongs with me since Honor 4x device, Obviously I was beta tester for Honor 4x Also selected As a Top Beta tester For Honor.N was a tester Forcustom Rom(Lewa Os)TIPS & TRICKS:- I'm Using Honor Device since 2k13, EMUI looke Friendly to meI would love to Maderate Under this sectionHONOR 9 LITE:- Obviously I want to moderate this section, as I'm using this device too & Handling some groups Related with this device. As an Admin(Own many groups)& user , I would like to support my Honor 9 lite Mates regarding this device & Solve their ProblemsRequirements:-Mentioned almost all, Just Try meThank You, Zoro & Honor TeamAdi HonorI remember you well :P  once a time I was part of your Honor Clan in Clash of Clan Game, I think you're that :D You're well deserved for becoming moderator :D Thank you My old friend :)Yea I remember you as well.We Enjoyed in CoC too ;) N was I. Impressed with our success in CoC :-pYou too deserve to become an moderator buddyBets of luckN thank you again Are you still playing that game ? :DNopeI left a year agoGood luck.

column1: [The fist batch list is annouced now] We are looking for Honor Community Moderators, Apply Here!
column2: 10Hi Everyone, My name is in blue aboveI'm Student, Tech enthusiast and fulfill all the requirements mentioned above.I'm very excited that our community is growing everyday, which has lead us here to the new moderator recruitment.I am here to apply for sectionsHONOR 6X & EMUI BETA.HONOR 6X_I bought it last year and I'm planning to use it for more than 2 years from now. I have knowledge about the better part of this device and happy to help other guys who are having any sorts of software problem with it.EMUI BETA _ I have experience of beta testing as I was beta tester in MEIZU's Flyme Forum for 2 years. I use my 6X pretty heavily and in almost all aspects. So I'll be happy to report any software bug that I encounter to provide the most stable experience to our customers.Thanks to Team Honor for the opportunity and Good Luck to everyone who have applied.Good Luck Raunak!All the very best dude
